==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: houhere
<hw>houhere</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A small tree or shrub (<spn>Hoheria
populnea</spn>) of New Zealand having a profusion of axillary clusters
of honey-scented paper-white flowers and whose bark is used for
cordage.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> lacebark, ribbonwood, <spn>Hoheria
populnea</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Houlet</ent>⟦br⟧
